Court finds the defendant was under the age of 25 at the time of the offense, the charge is a Misdemeanor, society would not be harmed and the defendant would benefit by expungement. Court would approve expungement upon successful completion of the following:
- Complete all terms of probation
- Follow all rules and recommended treatment by the agent
- Pay all costs, fees, assessments and surcharges owed during the term of probation (no amount to be converted to civil judgment)
- No violations of the law that rise to the level of probable cause

Sentencing proceeds.   State advises the Court they have complied with victim notification.  Statements by the State, defense counsel and defendant.  

COURT ORDERS defendant to serve  9  months at the House of Correction, Huber privileges and  34 days credit.  Defendant may earn good time credit.  COURT STAYS the sentence and places the defendant on probation for a period of  1 year.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:
- Anger Management evaluation and any recommended treatment
- Attend and successfully complete a Parenting class
- AODA assessment and any recommended treatment
- Absolute Sobriety
- Random screens
- No drugs without a valid prescription
- Court sets Restitution at $1,215.60
- Pay Restitution in the amount of $1,215.60 to David C. and pay any restitution surcharges
- No Contact Order with David C.
- Seek/Maintain employment
- Job/Vocational training
- No fine
- Pay costs, fees, assessments and surcharges (including DNA surcharge) during the term of probation.  Failure to pay all monies owed will result in a civil judgment.
